'''Giuseppe Weidmann''' (1742–1810) was an [[Austria]]n drama actor.

He was born in [[Vienna]]  to a poor family. He interrupted his studies to become an actor, and specialized in playing the ''grotesque'' stock characters, perhaps a [[Hanswurst]] for the theater in [[Brünn]]. After a spell in theaters in Vienna and [[Salzburg]]; in 1765, he began reciting comic parts for audiences in [[Prague]]. He produced a single drama, titled ''Sipper''; he performed then in [[Linz]] and Gratz; but was called by [[Emperor Joseph II]] to perform in Vienna. Weidmann was named one of five inspectors of the court theater.<ref>{{cite book| first=Filippo de'| last=Boni| year=1852| title=''Biografia degli artisti ovvero dizionario della vita e delle opere dei pittori, degli scultori, degli intagliatori, dei tipografi e dei musici di ogni nazione che fiorirono da'tempi più remoti sino á nostri giorni. Seconda Edizione.''| editor = | pages= 1089 | publisher=Presso Andrea Santini e Figlio|location=Venice; Googlebooks |id= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IU0_AAAAcAAJ&pg=PA441 | authorlink=}}</ref>

