The '''''Madonna of the Pomegranate''''' (''Madonna della Melagrana'') is a painting by the [[Italy|Italian]] [[Renaissance]] master [[Sandro Botticelli]], circa 1487. It is housed in the [[Uffizi|Uffizi Gallery]] of [[Florence]], Italy.
Several copies of the work exist, currently held at the [[Berlin]] [[Berlin State Museums|State Museums]], the [[Wernher Collection]] in [[London]] and the Aynard Collection at [[Lyon]].
